<div class="xar-mod-head"><span class="xar-mod-title"><xar:mlstring>AuthURL Administration</xar:mlstring></span></div>
<div class="xar-mod-body">
    <h2><xar:mlstring>Overview</xar:mlstring></h2>
        <div style="padding: 1px;" class="xar-norm-outline">
        <div style="float:right;padding:10px;">
        <xar:if condition="file_exists('modules/authurl/xarimages/admin.gif')" >
            <img src="modules/authurl/xarimages/admin.gif" alt="official icon" width="96" height="96" />
        <xar:else />
            <img src="modules/base/xarimages/admin_generic.gif" alt="official icon" width="96" height="96" />
        </xar:if>
        </div>
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            <xar:mlstring>The AuthURL module allows you to authenticate a user based on their access to another URL/site.  The AuthURL module sends a HTTP basic authentication request to the specified URL with the credentials supplied from the login form.</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>How to use it?</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            <xar:mlstring>Authentication by AuthURL is automatically set once the the AuthURL module has been initialized.  To remove AuthURL authentication, you must remove the module.</xar:mlstring>
            <br /><br />
            <xar:mlstring>
						From the menu, you have one choice.  "Modify Config".  From here, you:
						</xar:mlstring>
					<ul>
						<li><xar:mlstring>Set the URL to authenticate users against.</xar:mlstring></li>
						<li><xar:mlstring>Allow a user that successfully authenticates to be automatically added to the Xaraya database and allowed to login.</xar:mlstring></li>
						<li><xar:mlstring>Set the default group that users are added to if they are automatically created.</xar:mlstring></li>
						<li><xar:mlstring>Set the level of output that this module logs (useful for seeing what is happening under the hood).</xar:mlstring></li>
					</ul>
				</div>
        <br />
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>Included Blocks</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
			<xar:mlstring>There are no included blocks with the AuthURL Module</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div class="xar-norm-outline xar-accent" style="text-align: center; padding: 0.5em 1em 0.5em 1em; margin-top: 5px;">
            <xar:mlstring>Extended information about this module can be found here. [modules module]</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
